  "market_context": "After two days of large expansion, price approached the previous day high (PDH) during early New York session. A shallow run above PDH occurred, followed by a small wick and confirmed change in state of delivery, setting up a bearish reversal targeting equilibrium.",
  "key_observation": "A shallow opposing run above the previous day high formed a small wick (not large), and a change in state of delivery confirmed the reversal, supporting expansion lower toward equilibrium.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified previous day high (PDH) as the key point of interest for a potential reversal after two days of large expansion.",
    "Step 2: Observed a shallow run above PDH forming a small wick (not a large wick reversal candle), indicating potential for expansion rather than rejection.",
    "Step 3: Waited for confirmation via change in state of delivery (CISD) — price closing through opposing candles — to validate the reversal setup.",
    "Step 4: With CISD confirmed and small wick present, anticipated expansion lower with equilibrium (EQ) as the target zone.",
    "Step 5: Noted timing: reversal formed early enough in New York session to allow full expansion before day end."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price expanded lower and hit equilibrium (EQ) at the end of the day; next-day fractal model confirmed candle-2 closure with CISD, setting up candle-3 expansion.",
  "lessons": "Shallow runs above PDH with small wicks and confirmed CISD support high-probability reversals targeting EQ. Large wicks require adjusted targets toward daily open; small wicks support full expansion. Timing relative to NY session is critical.",
